      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, you are absolutely right! I was so busy trying to make the goblins relevant to your clothing shop that I forgot to tell you that the goblins are just as much part of your inventory as the clothes themselves!\n\nIf your inventory turnover is low, it means your clothes are sitting in your shop like a **goblin hoard** that you haven't even started to dig through yet. You are holding onto your money and your space for too long, and you are likely losing customers because your clothes are too heavy, too cold, or just too boring to wear.\n\nIn the goblin world, a low turnover means you are a **slow-witted goblin** who keeps the same pile of snowballs (your clothes) in the same spot for years instead of moving them to a new, warmer spot where they can be sold. You are essentially a **goblin with a slow metabolism**, and your shop is just a **goblin graveyard** where your clothes are rotting in the dirt because nobody is coming to pick them up.\n\nSo, if your ratio is low, you need to act like a **goblin with a sharp mind** and start moving your clothes around faster, or maybe you need to find",
